article.headline: Memphis 66, Tulsa 64
article.story:
MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Victoria Crawford hit two free throws with
1:25 left in the game and the Lady Tigers held off Tulsa for a
66-64 victory in the first round of the Women's National Invitation
Tournament Thursday night.

The Golden Hurricane (19-12) had a chance to tie or take the
lead in the game with 12 seconds remaining but Kara Pongonis' shot
never reached the rim.

Tulsa tied the game five times in the second half after trailing
37-35 at halftime. A layup by TaTanisha Wagoner at the 10:56 mark
allowed Tulsa to go ahead but Crawford's jumper five minutes later
put Memphis (21-9) ahead for good.

Pongonis led all scorers with 21 points, including five
3-pointers, while Jillian Robbins added 20 points and 10 rebounds.

Tamika Butler paced the Lady Tigers with 18 points and Crawford
finished with 17.

After trading baskets with Memphis early in the game, TU went on
a 12-2 run to take an 18-8 advantage at 12:48.

Memphis' full-court press allowed the Lady Tigers to get back
into the game, forcing 15 TU turnovers.

The Golden Hurricane tied the game at 35-35 on a jumper by Megan
Moody but Crawford's layup at the buzzer gave the Lady Tigers a
two-point advantage at intermission.
